Finally went to check this place out.  Same game plan as their better-known competitor whose name rhymes with frito-lay. Pluses: their steak is not hard near-beef jerkey like cubes, option to add guac to your food for $1 vs. $3 as a side (vs. the no-arbitrage pricing at the other place) , line moves quickly, and they offer hard taco "bits" that can be added for some extra crunch.  The negs: rice is flavorless yellow and dry, you have to pick your hot sauce and let them put it on (vs. letting you pick your own when done), and the room (at least this particular location) is super smoky and so even if you get takeout, you come out with that smoky aroma.  Overall, I didn't find it that much more compelling than frito-lay.  I guess when frito-lay gets over their problem with rhymes with "I'm not gonna lie", I'll probably go back.
